      <Desc>Residential Substance Abuse Treatment, Prevention and Education - Services provided include residential substance abuse treatment, transitional housing, and a continuum of behavioral health services in a residential setting, which are offered to the client occupants to meet their individual needs. The Oakland Lodge is a residential program for women with their children birth to 5 years old. In addition, an aftercare program provides ongoing individual and group counseling, case management, skill building, resume preparation, educational and job opportunities, and a clean and sober support network. This program is supported by program service revenue, government grants, and donations.</Desc>
