      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Board members sign-off on conflict of interest statements. In addition, board members attend an annual board retreat which provides an annual training, conducted by an attorney who advises the board about its duty of loyalty, which includes information about having, knowing and updating the written conflict of interest policy; saying no to loans between officers and directors; and the Organization and corporate opportunity rule-that directors can not divert opportunities from the Organization to themselves or others for their gain. Any related party transactions will be notified to the board of directors.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Friendship House Association of American Indians, Inc. (FHA) uses nonprofit wage and salary data for the SF Bay area to review upper management wages from time to time to ensure wages are within reasonable range for the size, location, and type of Organization.</ExplanationTxt>
